        <p>After losing my sense of purpose during service in the Royal Air Force, I turned my attention back to my historic passion: Astronomy! Whilst undertaking my undergraduate research at Birkeck College, I fell in love with all things exoplanetary, and regained my direction in life. The idea that all of these exoplanets are out in the cosmos, orbiting their stars, and just waiting
          for us to come along and find them had me totally hooked! To further my goals, I am currently undertaking an MSc in Space Exploration Systems at the University of Leicester. My ultimate goal is to undertake a PhD in exoplanet detection or the development of instrumentation specifically tailored to identifying the smallest, most challenging exoplanets to observe. If you share similar interests or just want to connect — connect with me on LinkedIn!
